<opener><salute>Dear Father/</salute></opener>
<p>The bearer, Coy. Sergt Maj.
<lb/> Hall is my Coy. Sergt Major. At least he is 
<lb/> C.S.M of "A" Coy. and a rattling good
<lb/> man. He can give you all the
<lb/> Battalion gossip. He will probably tell
<lb/> you he is having a lovely time now
<lb/> that he is temporarily rid of me as a
<lb/> Coy. Cmdr. He will also probably tell
<lb/> you that your son is a terribly
<lb/> hard man. He smokes.</p>
<closer><salute>Your affectionate son</salute>
<signed><hi rend="underline">Wm. Montgomery</hi></signed>
<date><hi rend="superscript">16/11/16</hi></date></closer>
        
    

    
        
        
        
    
                </body>
